(42, 2, 5, 5, 22, 22, 27, 'espoused wife', 'Connection of Betrothal and Consequences', 'Both passages emphasize the seriousness of betrothal and the consequences of infidelity. In Luke, Mary is described as ''espoused,'' while Deuteronomy outlines the severe penalties for violations of betrothal.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 5, 40, 1, 18, 19, 'Mary his espoused wife', 'Connection of Mary and Joseph', 'Both passages emphasize Mary as Joseph''s espoused wife and her pregnancy. This connection highlights the circumstances surrounding the birth of Jesus and Joseph''s response to Mary''s condition.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 6, 19, 33, 11, 11, 'the days were accomplished', 'Divine Timing and Counsel', 'This connection highlights the fulfillment of God''s plans, as seen in the timing of Jesus'' birth in Luke and the enduring nature of God''s counsel in Psalms. Both passages emphasize the certainty of God''s intentions across generations.', 'theme', 0.356, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 6, 33, 5, 2, 2, 'the days were accomplished that she should be delivered', 'Connection of Birthplace Prophecy', 'This connection highlights the fulfillment of prophecy regarding the birthplace of the ruler in Israel. Luke 2:6 indicates the time of Jesus'' birth, while Micah 5:2 specifically names Bethlehem as the prophesied location.', 'prophecy', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 6, 66, 12, 1, 5, 'should be delivered', 'Connection of Birth and Delivery', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of a woman in labor and the imminent delivery of a child. Luke 2:6 describes the fulfillment of the time for delivery, while Revelation 12:2 highlights the woman''s travailing in birth, connecting the two events of significant births.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 6, 20, 19, 21, 21, NULL, 'Divine Timing and Counsel', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine timing in both passages. Luke 2:6 speaks of the fulfillment of God''s plan in the birth of Jesus, while Proverbs 19:21 emphasizes that ultimately, it is the counsel of the Lord that prevails.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 6, 42, 1, 57, 57, 'the days were accomplished that she should be delivered', 'Connection of Birth Announcements', 'Both passages emphasize the fulfillment of time for childbirth. They highlight the moment when the expected delivery occurs for both Mary and Elisabeth.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 7, 48, 4, 4, 4, NULL, 'Connection of Birth and Timing', 'Both passages emphasize the arrival of God''s Son. Luke highlights the humble circumstances of His birth, while Galatians speaks to the divine timing of His coming.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 7, 47, 8, 9, 9, 'there was no room for them in the inn', 'Connection of Poverty and Humility', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus'' humble beginnings, as he was laid in a manger due to a lack of accommodation. Both passages emphasize his transition from wealth to poverty for the sake of humanity.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 7, 43, 1, 14, 14, 'laid him in a manger', 'Incarnation and Humility', 'This connection highlights the humble beginnings of Jesus, as seen in both passages. Luke describes His birth in a manger, while John emphasizes His incarnation as ''the Word made flesh.''', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 7, 23, 53, 2, 3, 'no room for them in the inn', 'Connection of Rejection and Humility', 'This connection highlights the theme of rejection and humble beginnings. In Luke, Jesus is laid in a manger due to lack of space, while Isaiah describes him as ''despised and rejected of men,'' emphasizing his lowly status and the lack of recognition he received.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 7, 40, 1, 25, 25, 'firstborn son', 'Connection of Firstborn Son', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of Jesus as the ''firstborn son.'' This connection highlights the continuity in the narrative of Jesus'' birth and identity.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 7, 40, 8, 20, 20, NULL, 'Jesus'' Humble Beginnings', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus'' lack of a stable home. Both passages emphasize the absence of a place for Jesus, first in a manger and later in his ministry.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 7, 42, 2, 11, 12, NULL, 'Connection of Birth and Sign', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of the babe wrapped in swaddling clothes and lying in a manger. This connection highlights the humble circumstances of Jesus'' birth as a sign for the shepherds.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 8, 1, 31, 39, 40, 'keeping watch over their flock by night', 'Shepherds and Night Vigil', 'Both passages emphasize the role of shepherds during the night. In Luke, the shepherds are watching their flock by night, while in Genesis, the speaker describes the challenges faced at night while tending to livestock.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 8, 9, 17, 34, 35, 'shepherds abiding in the field', 'Shepherding and Protection Theme', 'This connection highlights the role of shepherds in both passages. In Luke, the shepherds are vigilant over their flock, while in 1 Samuel, David demonstrates his protective nature as a shepherd by defending his sheep from predators.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 8, 19, 78, 70, 71, 'shepherds abiding in the field', 'Shepherd Imagery in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the role of shepherds. In Luke, the shepherds are present at Jesus'' birth, while in Psalms, David is chosen from the sheepfolds to lead God''s people, highlighting the significance of shepherding in biblical leadership.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 8, 43, 10, 8, 12, 'shepherds abiding in the field', 'Shepherd Imagery Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of shepherds, with Luke introducing shepherds watching over their flock and John presenting Jesus as the good shepherd who cares for the sheep. This connection highlights the protective and nurturing nature of shepherds in biblical imagery.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 8, 2, 3, 1, 2, 'shepherds abiding in the field', 'Shepherds and Divine Encounters', 'This connection highlights the role of shepherds in both passages, emphasizing their significance in divine encounters. In Luke, the shepherds are present at the announcement of Jesus'' birth, while in Exodus, Moses, a shepherd, encounters God at Horeb.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 8, 26, 34, 8, 8, 'shepherds abiding in the field', 'Shepherds and Their Flock', 'Both passages emphasize the role of shepherds in caring for their flock. Luke highlights shepherds watching over their sheep, while Ezekiel critiques shepherds who neglect their duty, leading to the flock''s suffering.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 9, 23, 60, 1, 1, 'the glory of the Lord', 'Connection of Divine Glory', 'Both passages emphasize the ''glory of the Lord.'' In Luke, the angel''s appearance is accompanied by this glory, while Isaiah calls for the light and glory of the Lord to shine upon the people.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 9, 47, 3, 18, 18, 'the glory of the Lord', 'Connection of Divine Glory', 'This connection highlights the theme of the ''glory of the Lord'' present in both passages. In Luke, the glory is a divine manifestation that evokes fear, while in 2 Corinthians, it represents transformation and change through the Spirit.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 9, 11, 8, 11, 11, 'the glory of the Lord', 'Connection of Divine Glory', 'Both passages emphasize the ''glory of the Lord'' manifesting in powerful ways, evoking fear and awe. In Luke, the glory surrounds the shepherds, while in Kings, it fills the temple, demonstrating God''s presence.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 9, 44, 27, 23, 23, 'the angel of the Lord', 'Angelic Presence in Crisis', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of an angel during moments of fear and uncertainty. In Luke, the angel brings a message of joy, while in Acts, the angel provides reassurance amidst danger.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 9, 66, 18, 1, 1, 'the glory of the Lord shone', 'Angelic Glory Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the glory of the Lord shining forth through angels. In Luke, the angel''s presence causes fear due to the glory surrounding them, while in Revelation, an angel''s glory lightens the earth.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 9, 2, 40, 34, 35, 'the glory of the Lord', 'Divine Glory Manifestation', 'Both passages emphasize the ''glory of the Lord'' as a powerful, overwhelming presence. In Luke, the glory surrounds the shepherds, while in Exodus, it fills the tabernacle, indicating God''s divine presence among His people.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 9, 7, 6, 11, 12, 'angel of the Lord', 'Divine Encounter with Fear', 'Both passages emphasize the appearance of an angel of the Lord, which evokes fear in the recipients. In Luke, the shepherds are ''sore afraid'' at the angel''s presence, while Gideon is reassured by the angel''s message of God''s presence.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 10, 23, 40, 9, 9, 'good tidings', 'Connection of Good Tidings', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of bringing good tidings and encourage a lack of fear. The angel''s message in Luke echoes the call in Isaiah to proclaim joy and strength to the people.', 'theme', 0.503, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 10, 23, 61, 1, 1, 'good tidings', 'Connection of Good Tidings', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of ''good tidings'' as a message of hope and joy. Luke 2:10 presents the angel''s announcement of joy for all people, while Isaiah 61:1 speaks of preaching good tidings to the meek, highlighting a shared message of liberation and comfort.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 10, 40, 28, 18, 18, 'good tidings of great joy', 'Joy and Authority Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of joy and power. The ''good tidings of great joy'' in Luke reflects the authority of Jesus, who states ''All power is given unto me'' in Matthew.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
